FBIS4-28807 "dreas114_a_94011" FBIS-EAS-94-114 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hata To Urge Continued Western Aid for Russia Hata To Urge Continued Western Aid for Russia OW1406033994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0323 GMT 14 Jun 94 OW1406033994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 14 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata indicated Tuesday [14 Jun] he will appeal for continued aid to Russia, eastern Europe and South Africa when he meets leaders of the Group of Seven (G-7) industrial nations at the Naples summit in July. Hata told the House of Councillors Budget Committee the developing countries would have serious difficulty in solving their various problems if the G-7 discontinued its aid. Britain, Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan and the United States are scheduled to take part in the summit.
